{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, this paper introduces a \"system architecture\" perspective, deconstructing the literature into core engines and auxiliary systems.",
    "This perspective enables us to keenly identify that the \"iterative repair loop\" is not merely a simple technical option but a key architectural component connecting probabilistic models with deterministic quality requirements.",
    "Furthermore, our analysis of future directions is more structured, systematically mapping identified challenges in quality, model limitations, and evaluation to three specific innovation paths of integration and synergy, autonomy and intelligence, and expansion and deepening.",
    "There are also some systematic reviews specifically addressing unit test generation using LLMs, which complement our analysis [162].In summary, this review bridges the cognitive gap between \"general LLM capabilities\" and \"specific test task implementation. \"",
    "By introducing a system engineering analysis framework, we not only depict the technical landscape of the field but also reveal its internal logic of evolving from single-point generation to closed-loop systems."
  ]
}